I had been a supporter of both Oprah and Dwayne Johnson, Jay-z and others, and it came to me that why should we keep giving money to ppl who already have enough while the rest of America is struggling? I have put several fundraisers up to help me with my daughter's college. I was trying to raise money( $3,800 of a $9,000 balance) so thst she could return to finish her junior year as a political science major. Well, that didn't happen. Since I lost my job due to health issues, that capped my financial help to null and void; and my heart grew cold towards family, friends, and ppl I general.  So why should ppl keep supporting ppl who can make more money with what they have while we struggle to make ends meet? Last night we had no food in our cabinet, so I made due what we had. Tearing up just thinking about it. Waiting for disability now for almost 10 months.  So please excuse me if I'm not jovial right now. (My comment is not up for discussion).

What an exchange of a beautiful inner spirit that Tracee Ellis Ross shared her singing for her mom for the first time.  This was such a defining moment she and her mom shared.  How very special for the two of them and how greatly appreciated her sharing publicly.  The fact that she captured the very reason as to why being afraid/fearful about was to trying something new and different .  Something that would take her out of her comfort zone.  All young people need to see this, read and her her comments. “You work to keep pace with the earth and the soul of the earth.For to be idle is to become a stranger into the seasons and to step out of life’s procession that marches in majesty and proud submission towards the infinite.” Kahlil GibranSo I leave us all with this thought:  I am 72 years old. I am symptomatic with the virus, but I still take deep breaths, and my inhaler is keeping me clear. I also have a massive kidney infection, diabetes and an autoimmune disorder. To add to that, I am allergic to nearly all antibiotics...no joke...I can only take two different ones, everything else is no. I will not go to the hospital to be tested if I can no longer breath, or my kidneys explode. It makes no sense for me to go where sick people are, and risk my immune system further. I wash my hands a lot, I don’t touch my daughter or husband who are both still healthy, and I sanitize a everything I touch except for my dogs. I have been sequestered for almost two weeks, except for seeing the urologist in his private office while I wore a mask. I have lived through worse. Sorry to hear about Italy. Sorry for everywhere. I worry the most about the homeless. Most shelters have closed their doors, as have most churches. Some of the food banks are open, but many soup kitchens are closing. Here the schools have been putting together breakfast for low income families, and lunches. Kids that live in the area we live in, the busses are delivering meals to the bus stops. If you live less than two miles from the school, you have to pick the bag of food up in the morning and at lunch. The homeless don’t have access that food unless they have a child in school. My daughter and I usually hand out meals and supplies for the homeless out of my own pocket (no we don’t have a lot of money), but I can’t hand out food or supplies now. I can’t even do that much. Have any ideas for the homeless? It’s heart breaking!💔😢

I have always admired you and the way you use your platform to promote the well-being of people and our world. I couldn't believe that with all of your experience and knowledge and resources that not only were you promoting diet culture, but that I later found out you had invested tons of money into it (had to do a Google search when I got home, because, again, I almost couldn't believe it). This may seem like a trivial topic amid what is currently going on, but it matters. How do you take this type of criticism? What is your response? I'm open to hearing it; I'm curious with an open heart. Why can't you dream up (or find what's probably already out there) a program for women that costs as much as WW but is about empowerment instead? I'm not saying you don't support (probably a thousand of) those, but WHY WW? WHY?  Sincerely, a woman in Wyoming trying constantly to escape diet culture, change the conversation, and recover from an eating disorder (Caiti)

I love this answer (borrowed from a friend) PSA: There is nothing genetically inferior about Black people that is making them more susceptible to this virus, and to believe otherwise is racist. The reason Black people are disproportionately infected and dying from Coronavirus is systemic and structural racism and I sincerely wish that the media would just use those words to describe the issue.1) Black Americans are less likely to be tested for the virus than their white counterparts2) Black Americans are less likely to be treated for the virus than their white counterparts3) Black Americans are more likely to be "essential workers" and have to keep going into work, meaning disproportionate exposure to the virus 4) Black Americans are more likely to come from socioeconomic backgrounds where they are forced to take public transportation, meaning disproportionate exposure to the virus5) Black Americans are less likely to have access to quality healthcare, period. 6) When Black Americans have access to even the best healthcare, study after study shows their concerns are taken less seriously than the concerns of their white counterparts. 7) Many of the underlying conditions that Black Americans suffer from which make them more likely to die from the virus are due to deeper, structural inequities (such as living in food deserts, lacking access or resources to necessary preventative care, etc). The media is doing a terrible job reporting and explaining this multifaceted issue and in doing so, they are encouraging audiences to develop their own racist ideas about the genetic inferiority or superiority of people based on race.

Hello, Oprah. Thank you for this beautiful, thoughtful message. It had me bawling for it's unifying message of the difficulty we have all felt during these times. To see you put it so eloquently into WORDS is edifying and gives me hope. I am more saddened than my own 2020 graduate not to be able to attend the long-awaited graduation ceremony at Swarthmore in the beautiful Pennsylvania arboretum! The culmination of all those days and nights I spent with her filling out admissions forms and financial aid forms and more forms and papers - I needed to see that come down to that moment where we could all come together to celebrate all of our hard work. Now it will be spent at home watching some sort of graduation ceremony on our TV, just many faces of the graduates popping by, one after the other, likely some music and words from the President. But as with all things we need to focus above and beyond on the things that really matter. To set our sights on greater things. To create our own special, magical moments. I have been inspired. Thank you!

Abstract Human body activity associated with a task provided to a user may be used in a mining process of a cryptocurrency system. A server may provide a task to a device of a user which is communicatively coupled to the server. A sensor communicatively coupled to or comprised in the device of the user may sense body activity of the user. Body activity data may be generated based on the sensed body activity of the user. The cryptocurrency system communicatively coupled to the device of the user may verify if the body activity data satisfies one or more conditions set by the cryptocurrency system, and award cryptocurrency to the user whose body activity data is verified.Also published as WO/2020/060606

The Gardena police interrogated him while he was medicated by the hospital and gave him 40 years to life for a DUI. Nobody died. But they gave him life. My non-profit helps felons get jobs and help with legal assistance. We are suffering out here but people think we not trying. Every corner I turn i see death. People here have PTSD and mental illnesses that stem from the police and gangs. I hope someone reading this understands, we dont care about new music or movies. I was married with my first child at 18, my second child at age 21, thrown from a car at 22, divorced by 23 and remarried at 25, completed my BS in Psychology, MS in Counseling Psychology and while at the same graduate school entered into a Ph.d of Psychology program and made all the way to comps to be told I did not write my comps exam as expected. I had many years of writing at that school and never failed a paper but when I shared I was having sickness they took advantage of the moment and would ask what my race was during conversation. I have $189,000 student loan debt, unable to get a home for my family size of 7 now because of student loan debt and income to debt ratio, someone keeps putting negative things on my credit, and I dound out the programs completed does not meet standards for licensure in my major field in their state nor mines and has been limited to become a licensed clinical addiction specialist associate. Now due to covid I am unable to keep a supervisor. I have worked three jobs as a Behavioral Health Specialist, Adjunct Professor of Psychology, and Consultant for 11 to 14 years and wasn't afforded the ability to do anything when I had to got out on disability and I have seen many whites given so much flexibility. I turned 40 this year in hopes to have my dream home, but that didn't happen. Income has went down to poverty-stricken and I have been sick still trying. No one to help. Sometimes I see why my patients feel that dying is the best solution. We are all human but treat each other worse than we would animals. So hurt by the mirage of social injustice, limited resources, and racial discrimination. Many of my clients could have good lives with resources. Resources, love, and support is the true therapy and solution to our world crisis, but never addressed due to the feeling of giving a handout. Isn't donations handouts? Handouts that give temporary  solutions to problems people feel. Blacks are so deprived. We don't be positive and support each other because there is so much hurt and bitterness. Lives are loss but there are so many here to be helped and saved from more than death.
